The best Thai food in the area! The family that runs this place is so nice and the food is authentic. Fried fish in particular is very satisfying. And the portion of mango sticky rice was HUGE!

Babgkok Thai Dining is a family operated - authentic Thai restaurant. Service is excellent! Food is good, very tasty and prices are reasonable. Apps, soups, shrimp fried rice, deserts....all are flavorful. The menu has a variety of options. I would say it’s a great choice for lunch when in Dupont Circle neighborhood.

Really poor. They put broccoli in the Tom Yum and flavour is bland. Worst papaya salad I have ever had, not even remotely spicy. Pad Thai came with no Chili or lime and was also bland. Pork curry was ok in terms of sauce but pork was over cooked. Mango sticky rice had tart and not tasty mango. Even white rice was not very good. Much better options in the area.

This spot is my favorite. I go to many restaurants but to this one I  constantly return again and again. The team is very attentive and the cuisine they place on your table is so good. I would always prefer to have a decent dinner in this place. I highly recommend this place.

Yummy yummy yummy yummy delicious
Best Thai restaurant in DC! We have eaten here multiple times and have never been disappointed. Food is fresh and delicious, service is quick and staff are always friendly.
The food was good and the service was good!

We’ve been ordering take out weekly here for almost a year. We love the Chicken Pad See Ew, Red Curry and Curry Puffs. In 50+ take out orders (ugh yes we may have a problem), they have never messed up our order. Exemplary customer service - everyone is kind. In the pandemic world, all are wearing masks and following social distancing measures. Highly recommend supporting this great local business!
I really loved their food and customer service, great area  to my residence. The employees are always super nice. Will visit here again.
The red curry was very bland and watery. Will not be ordering from here again.
I got the drunken noodles tonight for carry out, and it was amazing!! I’ve tried the green curry as well, and that was great too. The prices are pretty good and priced accurately for what you get.

This place is a gem! We went there last month during our Spring break trip to D.C.. Their foods were so good that we had to come back for the second time. We are from Thailand. And we have tried Thai foods around the U.S. We can say that this restaurant is on our top list. We tried their Pad Thai and Pad See Ew. They even tasted better than many Thai restaurants in Thailand. Highly recommended!
Lovely place serving up good portions of quality food.

This place is average. I ordered a Massamun Curry in medium spicy which was good for who love spicy food like me (the spiciness is a Thai standard so it might be spicier that you’d expect). The vegetables in the curry was weirdly proportioned - there was like one piece of bell pepper, one piece of green bean, and a lot of onions lol. Not that it affects the flavor but just found it odd and funny. I definitely love the Massamun curry, it was very rich and flavorful.  My boyfriend ordered a Pad Thai chicken which the sauce/flavor was good but there was no vegetables included except bean sprouts and green onions. We were expecting to have some carrots, maybe peppers or chives and lime but didn’t have those.  The servers were very nice and friendly. One other thing was that the bathroom was gross. If someone went there before the meal or in between, they probably will lose their appetite. Luckily, I went after my meal.
Bad, stingy service.
Had a very good experience here with my kid. The food arrived quick and the service is just awesome. Prices are convenient.
I adore this restaurant a lot. there is a happy spirit. The kitcen is splendid. the service is efficient and the stuff is very professional. The pay is fair. I warmly recommend.
Wonderful quaint restaurant. The spice in the food was right oomph target to what I asked for. I will definitely come back!

Excellent small Thai restaurant with very friendly staff and excellent food, with decent prices for the area. My favorites are their Thai red curry dishes. Mix the rice and the rest of the dish together, and it's heavenly. Don't order more than mild spiciness unless you are prepared!
Food was so tasty, the service was pleasant and fast and prices were very reasonable

Best Thai place that serves most authentic thai food. Service is fast. Food is delicious.  Thai crab fried rice is our favorite along with red curry chicken. We highly recommend this place to anyone around Maryland/DC looking for a good Thai restaurant.

This is my go to Thai restaurant in DC. The location can be easily missed. It is a basement restaurant. I've never had to make reservations. The food is excellent and on point. The spice level definitely needs to be explained to the server to ensure your food is not spicy hot. I am a fan of spicy food and order "Medium Spicy" and it is the perfect level. The servers are always nice and attentive.  I recommend for a quick bite for lunch or for a not so intimate dinner.

Really great, cozy and friendly thai restaurant near DuPont circle! The food at Bangkok was excellent; I had the Thai green salad and Chicken Drunken Noodle which was wonderfully spiced and flavored. The staff was very nice, and the atmosphere was very cozy. Highly recommend if you like Thai food, and especially if you want a nice intimate restaurant without a lot of noise where you can get food without a long wait.

The service was good and the food was pretty good, middle-of-the-road Thai food in DC.  I was disappointed mostly by the portions (they charged dinner-sized prices for lunch-sized portions).  Not bad but not great either, and there is better available for that price.
Absolutely amazing... the food here is great. Its not always easy to find good Thai food but let me assure you the food here is great. Spicy level is 1 - 5.

Average Thai food with below average ambiance and poor service. Hard to understand the positive reviews here since there is definitely better Thai here in DC. Only thing going for it are the cheap prices.

Delicious food, great service, nice atmosphere. My friend and I ordered the Pad Ga Prao and oh man was it spicy - definitely hit my upper limit on heat tolerance. But the food was perfect, fresh, and we will definitely return. Highly recommend for those seeking spicy Thai food, but a word of caution: they aren't messing around with the 1, 2, and 3 chili pepper heat ratings. 3 is HOT! See you next week, Bangkok Thai!

Best Thai food in Washington. As good as the food in Thailand.

The food and drinks were delicious. I got the pad Thai - spicy and whoo it hit the spicy spot. My fiance got panang curry - spice level medium. We wanted to see how spicy the spice levels were. Spicy means you can really handle the heat. Both were delicious. The mai thai and the spiked Thai tea were flavorful. I'd go back again.

I was walking along P street when I saw the sign for the $9.99 lunch special and suddenly got a craving for Thai food.  The pad ga prao was delicious and the Thai iced tea was perfect with it.  I had the chicken and asked for mild spice, which was perfectly seasoned for me.  Not a tear was shed. The regular lunch menu doesn't cost much more than the special and has more than three items to choose from.  Good place for lunch after spending time at the Phillips.  It's in the basement so you have to walk down a small flight of stairs.
Loved this place! Authentic, great atmosphere, great service and dessert was to die for.  We’re visiting D.C. from NY.  Will definitely come back!

THE BEST THAI FOOD IN THE DMV!  I've been visiting this restaurant for years.  Last time I was here was six years ago due to location change.  I've known the owners for almost 20 years. It's a well lit place located in the basement.  If you've never visited, what are you waiting for?
Another great Thai restaurant in DC areas.   The food was excellent.  Highly recommend it to everyone.   @ Bangkok Thai Dining

The chicken satay and the panang curry are delicious. Probably the best panang curry I’ve had in DC. Rich coconut sauce and they don’t skimp on spice! However, I’ve ordered the pad Thai twice and it’s not good at all - barely any flavor (there’s a sauce on it but doesn’t taste like anything really, not even soy?) and there are never more than one or two vegetables (not types of vegetables, but actual pieces of vegetables in the side) so it’s mostly just bland noodles. But the other stuff was good!

Loved the broth of green curry! It was very tasty but didn’t like the cucumber and egg plant in the curry..and had really little bit of bamboos..wish they give a lot of bamboos!  Pad thai was pretty horrible. I seriously wanted to send the dish back to the kitchen because it tasted burnt and had no flavor. It was pretty bad.  Service was not good. It was hard to reach out to them and was very slow. My server wasn’t nice or kind either.  The restaurant had some bad smell when I first entered the door..and people who were eating there while I was there were pretty LOUD and seemed a bit drunk..so it was hard to enjoy the meal. I wouldn’t come back for the food if I’m honest.  So..overall, it’s overrated! Can’t agree with this one😨 (I have this amazing Thai restaurant called “Tida Thai” near where I live so it’s possible that I’m spoiled..lol) Other reviews made me expect TOO MUCH for this one! Had chicken satay, papaya salad, basil fried rice, and a few other dishes whose names I don't know.all of them were very tasty.   Medium spice on their scale is pretty spicy so beware about choosing their "hot" option.

teensy weensy portion of rice! When you pay $15 for a carry out meal you expect enough rice. unfortunatly that is not what you get here. You get something that is about 1/4 of the size that should be appropriate considering the price and portion of the main item. I have asked them to provide more rice before but get an attitude and they say I should pay an additional $2 for more rice! for the price of rice they should provide a commesurate amount. look at the picture, you get maybe 1/4 cup of rice post-cooked that is NOT ENOUGH. The annoying part is that I get home and have to fire up the pan and cook more rice. This is unacceptable. I come here often but have decided to not come here again until they stop pinching pennies and provide the correct amount of rice.

Excellent green papaya salad, which brought back so many memories of this wonderful dish in Bangkok, and made hot enough to tingle the taste buds.  Followed by seafood in a lemongrass/coconut curry, all of which tasted fresh and delicious, accompanied by a cold Singha.  Reminded me of small places in Bangkok and prices were very reasonable.  A great find in the DuPont Circle area.

I love their food and I only wish they were closer to my office so I can go more often for lunch. I go once a month for lunch when I'm up for a long walk. I've also been there for dinner. The restaurant is small and quaint and the ambiance won't blow you away but the food is great. If you go, you have to try the crab fried rice. They give you enough for four people so it can be ordered for the table. I order it for lunch as a second dish knowing I will be taking it home for my teenage son to devour. He loves it as well. He would eat it every day if he could. Prices are pretty reasonable for that area as well.
